<TITLE> ADB signs $150m loan for better governance in Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 1 (bdnews24.com) - The Asian Development Bank allocated the Bangladesh government $150 million in loans Thursday to assist in the fight against corruption and improve systems of governance. ADB country director Hua Du and secretary of the Economic Relations Division Aminul Islam Bhuiyan signed the deal. According to the ADB, the loan will also be used to support reform of the judiciary and strengthen the role and reach of the Anticorruption Commission. "The result will be a set of long-term policy reforms in good governance, particularly those related to instituting good practices in combating corruption," the ADB said. The ADB country chief also praised the separation of the judiciary from the executive. "It's a historical and brave step. I think it will benefit the people of Bangladesh," she said. The ADB loan will be released in three phases over the next four years. bdnew
